This document explains how to get a working installation of /etc/net
on a Fedora Core 5 or Fedora Core 6 system.

Step 1. Install the system and all updates.

Step 2. Backup your configuration

Step 3. Setup external repository:

# wget -o /etc/yum.repos.d/etcnet.repo http://etcnet.org/repo/etcnet.repo

Step 4. yum install etcnet
You should be prompted to install "etcnet" and to update "initscripts".
